  "title": "FOOD OUTLET MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Operational Management:</strong> Oversee day-to-day operations, including opening/closing, cleanliness, and ambiance to ensure smooth functioning.</li><li><strong>Customer Service:</strong> Address customer inquiries and complaints promptly, ensuring high satisfaction levels.</li><li><strong>Financial & Performance Control:</strong> Maximize revenue, manage budgets, control costs, and analyze service quality.</li><li><strong>Inventory & Purchasing:</strong> Manage stock levels, conduct inventory checks, and order supplies to prevent shortages or excesses.</li><li><strong>Team Leadership:</strong> Recruit, train, schedule, and motivate staff to maintain high service standards.</li><li><strong>Compliance:</strong> Ensure compliance with health, safety, and hygiene regulations. </li></ul><p><strong>Candidate Profile</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Experience:</strong> Generally requires 2–8 years of experience in food and beverage, culinary, or hospitality management.</li></ul>",
